08/10/2009
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Border police detained 21 illegal immigrants in the Adriatic Sea as they tried to leave Montenegrin territorial waters, local media reported on Wednesday (October 7th). 
Among the group arrested on Tuesday are 16 Albanian citizens and three Kosovo nationals, as well as two Serb crew members. 
The immigrants were allegedly bound for Italy. 
(Pobjeda, RTS, AP - 07/10/09)
